                                         CAPE TOWN - Miss South Africa Demi-Leigh Nel-Peters says that she's humbled and proud to be crowned Miss Universe.  The announcement was made early on Monday morning at a star-studded ceremony in Las Vegas. The 22-year-old from Sedgefield in the Western Cape is the second South African to ever win the crown after Margaret Gardiner in 1978.  Nel-peters has dedicated her award to South Africa. “[South] Africa, I love you. Thank you for everything. I am Miss Universe and this is for you.”  The second runner-up was miss Jamaica and the first runner-up was Miss Columbia.   (Edited by Shimoney Regter)